{{Quote|Outside the region, the small Cygnus Star Empire lies along on the Oktos Route in the Mid Rim, just coreward of Hutt Space. A handful of marginal worlds only a few parsecs apart, this Empire is believed to have once been the heart of a generous bribe made by the Hutt Clan-General, Kossak, that led several of Xim's allies to defect. Like their cousins in the Tion Cluster, the people there still use Tionese for special occasions.|Extract from a history of the Tionese language first published in the Imperial Period|<ref name="TWW">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/source/writtenword/index.html?page=1|text=The Written Word|int=The Written Word}}</ref>}}
The '''Cygnus Star Empire''' was an interplanetary state that straddled the [[Oktos Route]] in the [[Mid Rim/Legends|Mid Rim]] and lay immediately coreward of [[Hutt Space/Legends|Hutt Space]].

==History==
The Star Empire was located on the [[Oktos Route]] in the [[Mid Rim/Legends|Mid Rim]]. The region consisted of a handful of systems a few [[Parsec/Legends|parsecs]] wide. Due to its closeness to [[Hutt Space/Legends|Hutt Space]], just coreward of the region, it was believed to have originally been a bribe offered to several of [[Xim/Legends|Xim's]] allies by the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] warlord [[Kossak Inijic Ar'durv|Kossak]] during the [[Xim Wars]].

The [[Cygnus Spaceworks/Legends|Cygnus Spaceworks]] ship manufacturers were headquartered within the empire's domain, and the region was known to use [[Tionese/Legends|Tionese]] lettering, much like the [[Tion Cluster/Legends|Cluster]] itself.

==Behind the scenes==
The Cygnus Star Empire apparently originates in the fan-made work ''[[Book of Imperial Shuttle Plans: Cygnus Spaceworks]]'', published almost two decades before the name was referenced in [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] material. In ''Imperial Shuttle Plans'', the Cygnus Star Empire was associated with Cygnus Spaceworks and a Cygnus system. The Spaceworks was later referenced in Legends, in the [[Star Wars Technical Journal of the Imperial Forces|''Star Wars Technical Journal'']] and the video game [[Star Wars: TIE Fighter (video game)|''Star Wars: TIE Fighter'']]. A "human Star Empire" was mentioned in the unlicensed [[1998]] [[InQuest 39|''InQuest Gamer'' #39]] article "[[Terminators: Five Movie Monsters to Torment Your PCs]]" by [[Kenneth Hite]].<ref name="IG">[[InQuest 39|''InQuest'' 39]] - "[[Terminators: Five Movie Monsters to Torment Your PCs]]"</ref>

